<div class="context">
<h1 class="title">Variables</h1>
<span class="subtitle"></span>
<!-- $$$mkspecs-variable-reference.html-description -->
<div class="descr"> <a name="details"></a>
<a name="boost"></a>
<h2 id="boost">BOOST</h2>
<p>Specifies a list of Boost modules that are linked to this target. An additional variable member is available to define the type of dependency:</p>
<div class="table"><table class="generic">
 <thead><tr class="qt-style"><th >Member</th><th  colspan="2" rowspan=" 1">Value</th></tr></thead>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td  rowspan=" 3"><code>CONFIG</code></td><td ><code>shared</code></td><td ><b><i>by default:</i></b> modules are linked dynamically to this target (ignored for static library project).</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>static</code></td><td >modules are linked statically to this target (ignored for static library project).</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>combined</code></td><td >modules are combined to this target in case of static library project; otherwise is same as <code>static</code> value.</td></tr>
</table></div>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">BOOST.CONFIG += static   # Boost libraries will be linked statically
BOOST += log graph       # link to Boost Log and Graph libraries</pre>
<p>See also <a href="mkspecs-predefined-rules.html#boost-support">Boost Support</a>.</p>
<a name="boost-root"></a>
<h2 id="boost-root">BOOST_ROOT</h2>
<p>Contains the path to the Boost root directory. This variable is empty if:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>BOOST_ROOT</code> environment variable is not defined.</li>
<li>Boost feature is not supported by current platform and build environment.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="boost-includedir"></a>
<h2 id="boost-includedir">BOOST_INCLUDEDIR</h2>
<p>Contains the path to the directory containing Boost's headers. This variable is empty if <a href="mkspecs-variable-reference.html#boost-root">BOOST_ROOT</a> is not defined.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="boost-librarydir"></a>
<h2 id="boost-librarydir">BOOST_LIBRARYDIR</h2>
<p>Contains the path to the directory containing separately-compiled Boost libraries. This variable is empty if <a href="mkspecs-variable-reference.html#boost-root">BOOST_ROOT</a> is not defined.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="boost-version"></a>
<h2 id="boost-version">BOOST_VERSION</h2>
<p>Contains the current version of Boost. This variable is empty if Boost version cannot be resolved.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="iquotepath"></a>
<h2 id="iquotepath">IQUOTEPATH</h2>
<p>Specifies the headers directory paths to the list of directories to be searched for header files, only for the case of <code>#include &quot;file&quot;</code>. To lookup for <code>#include &lt;file&gt;</code> directives, use <code>INCLUDEPATH</code> variable instead.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">IQUOTEPATH *= C:/myproject/sources</pre>
<p>Specific quoted headers search paths is currently only supported by GCC compilers. For Visual C++ compiler, directories is append to <code>INCLUDEPATH</code> variable.</p>
<a name="installdir"></a>
<h2 id="installdir">INSTALLDIR</h2>
<p>Specifies the directory where project files will be installed.</p>
<p>See also <a href="mkspecs-predefined-rules.html#installation-definition">Installation Definition</a>.</p>
<a name="librarypath"></a>
<h2 id="librarypath">LIBRARYPATH</h2>
<p>Specifies the directories where archiver or linker will search for archives and shared libraries to link into the project.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">win32: LIBRARYPATH *= &quot;C:/mylibs/extra libs&quot;
linux: LIBRARYPATH *= &quot;/home/user/extra libs&quot;</pre>
<a name="literal-quotes"></a>
<h2 id="literal-quotes">LITERAL_QUOTES</h2>
<p>Useless from <b>qmake 3.0 (Qt 5.0)</b>. This variable is used whenever a literal double quote (<code>&quot;</code>) is needed in a variable declaration, and which would not be interpreted as such by qmake parser.</p>
<a name="literal-open-brace"></a>
<h2 id="literal-open-brace">LITERAL_OPEN_BRACE</h2>
<p>Useless from <b>qmake 3.0 (Qt 5.0)</b>. This variable is used whenever a literal open brace (<code>{</code>) is needed in a variable declaration, and which would not be interpreted as such by qmake parser.</p>
<a name="literal-close-brace"></a>
<h2 id="literal-close-brace">LITERAL_CLOSE_BRACE</h2>
<p>Useless from <b>qmake 3.0 (Qt 5.0)</b>. This variable is used whenever a literal close brace (<code>}</code>) is needed in a variable declaration, and which would not be interpreted as such by qmake parser.</p>
<a name="plugins"></a>
<h2 id="plugins">PLUGINS</h2>
<p>Specifies a list of shared libraries path that are not linked into the project but may be loaded dynamically at runtime. Note that each library must be passed with its full path.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">win32: PLUGINS *= &quot;../myplugins/plugin.dll&quot;
linux: PLUGINS *= &quot;../myplugins/libplugin.so&quot;</pre>
<p>The list of libraries stored in <code>PLUGINS</code> is reduced to a list of unique names.</p>
<a name="properties"></a>
<h2 id="properties">PROPERTIES</h2>
<p>Specifies target informations to be passed to the application if the app template is specified, or the library if the lib template is specified. The allowed values are:</p>
<div class="table"><table class="generic">
 <thead><tr class="qt-style"><th >Member</th><th >Description</th></tr></thead>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>name</code></td><td >The display name of application / library. Defaults to <code>TARGET</code> if empty.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>version</code></td><td >The target version number. Defaults to <code>unversioned</code> if empty or invalid. <br />
 <code>VERSION</code>, <code>VER_MAJ</code>, <code>VER_MIN</code> and <code>VER_PAT</code> variables are overridden by this version number, or reset to <code>0</code> if property is equals to <code>unversioned</code>.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>product</code></td><td >The product name for the project target. Defaults to <code>TARGET</code> if empty. <br />
 <i>Windows only:</i> <code>QMAKE_TARGET_PRODUCT</code> variable is overridden by this property.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>description</code></td><td >The target description. <br />
 <i>Windows only:</i> <code>QMAKE_TARGET_DESCRIPTION</code> variable is overridden by this property.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>company</code></td><td >The name of the organization (i.e&#x2e; company or author) publishing the project target. <br />
 <i>Windows only:</i> <code>QMAKE_TARGET_COMPANY</code> variable is overridden by this property.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>domain</code></td><td >The internet domain for the organization (taken into account if <code>company</code> property is set).</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>year</code></td><td >The target publication year. Defaults to current year if empty.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>copyright</code></td><td >The copyright information for the project target. This variable allows <code>%c</code> and <code>%y</code> modifiers respectively replaced with company and year properties. <br />
 <i>Windows only:</i> <code>QMAKE_TARGET_COPYRIGHT</code> variable is overridden by this property.</td></tr>
</table></div>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">PROPERTIES.name = MyApp
PROPERTIES.version = 1.2.3
PROPERTIES.company = Diginext
PROPERTIES.domain = diginext.fr
PROPERTIES.copyright = Copyright (C) %y %c</pre>
<p><b>Note: </b>Windows resource file generation requires <b>qmake 3.0 (Qt 5.0)</b> or later. Previous versions use <b>verpatch</b> tool to update target version and properties.</p><p>Moreover, qmake generates <code>info_$${TARGET}.h</code> and <code>info_$${TARGET}.cpp</code> source files in intermediate directory <code>generated/$${<a href="mkspecs-variable-reference.html#toolkit">TOOLKIT</a>.mkspec}/${<a href="mkspecs-pseudo-variable-reference.html#library-mode">LIBRARY_MODE</a>}/${<a href="mkspecs-pseudo-variable-reference.html#build-mode">BUILD_MODE</a>}/info</code>, in order to:</p>
<ul>
<li>access to these properies in the application or library source code.</li>
<li>initialize following <code>QCoreApplication</code> properties in case of case of Qt application.</li>
</ul>
<div class="table"><table class="generic">
 <thead><tr class="qt-style"><th >Property</th><th >Initialized with</th></tr></thead>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>applicationName</code></td><td ><code>PROPERTIES.name</code></td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>applicationVersion</code></td><td ><code>PROPERTIES.version</code></td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>organizationDomain</code></td><td ><code>PROPERTIES.domain</code></td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>organizationName</code></td><td ><code>PROPERTIES.company</code></td></tr>
</table></div>
<p>Below the source code of <code>info_$${TARGET}.h</code> generated by qmake:</p>
<pre class="cpp"><span class="preprocessor">#ifndef INFO_{TARGETNAME}_H</span>
<span class="preprocessor">#define INFO_{TARGETNAME}_H</span>

<span class="keyword">namespace</span> {TargetName} {

    <span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="type">char</span> <span class="operator">*</span> name();            <span class="comment">// returns PROPERTIES.name value</span>
    <span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="type">char</span> <span class="operator">*</span> version();         <span class="comment">// returns PROPERTIES.version value</span>
    <span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="type">char</span> <span class="operator">*</span> product();         <span class="comment">// returns PROPERTIES.product value</span>
    <span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="type">char</span> <span class="operator">*</span> organization();    <span class="comment">// returns PROPERTIES.company value</span>
    <span class="keyword">const</span> <span class="type">char</span> <span class="operator">*</span> copyright();       <span class="comment">// returns PROPERTIES.copyright value</span>

}

<span class="preprocessor">#endif</span></pre>
<p><i>Before Qt 5.1:</i> additional function <code>void setup( QCoreApplication * )</code> is provided to initialize <code>QCoreApplication</code> properties, since automatic initialization on application startup is not supported.</p>
<a name="qmake-ext-app"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-app">QMAKE_EXT_APP</h2>
<p>Contains the default extension used on applications.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="qmake-ext-ico"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-ico">QMAKE_EXT_ICO</h2>
<p>Windows only. Contains the extension used on icon files.</p>
<a name="qmake-ext-implib"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-implib">QMAKE_EXT_IMPLIB</h2>
<p>Windows only. Contains the default extension used on import libraries.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="qmake-ext-qml"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-qml">QMAKE_EXT_QML</h2>
<p>Contains suffixes for files which should be interpreted as QML files.</p>
<a name="qmake-ext-qrc"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-qrc">QMAKE_EXT_QRC</h2>
<p>Contains the extension used on Qt resource collection files.</p>
<a name="qmake-ext-shlib"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-shlib">QMAKE_EXT_SHLIB</h2>
<p>Contains the default extension used on shared libraries.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="qmake-ext-staticlib"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-staticlib">QMAKE_EXT_STATICLIB</h2>
<p>Contains the default extension used on static libraries.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="qmake-ext-ts"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-ext-ts">QMAKE_EXT_TS</h2>
<p>Contains the extension used on Qt Linguist translation files.</p>
<a name="qmake-metadata-generators"></a>
<h2 id="qmake-metadata-generators">QMAKE_METADATA_GENERATORS</h2>
<p>Specifies a list of additional metadata generators.</p>
<p>See also <a href="mkspecs-metadata-generation.html">Metadata Generation</a>.</p>
<a name="qml-files"></a>
<h2 id="qml-files">QML_FILES</h2>
<p>Specifies the names of all QML files in the project.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">QML_FILES = MainWindow.qml \
            Page1.qml Page2.qml</pre>
<p><b>Note: </b>QML files registration requires <b>qmake 3.0 (Qt 5.0)</b> or later.</p><a name="qsmakepath"></a>
<h2 id="qsmakepath">QSMAKEPATH</h2>
<p>Contains the path to the root directory containing the QS qmake features. Note that features files reside within a mkspecs sub-directory (i.e&#x2e; <code>$${QMAKEPATH}/mkspecs/&lt;features&gt;</code>), as required by Qt framework.</p>
<p>For example, the following line causes the location of the directory containing the QS qmake features to be written to the console:</p>
<pre class="cpp">message( $${QSMAKEPATH} )</pre>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p><a name="toolkit"></a>
<h2 id="toolkit">TOOLKIT</h2>
<p>Provides information about platform and build environment taken into account to generate the project target:</p>
<div class="table"><table class="generic">
 <thead><tr class="qt-style"><th >Member</th><th >Value</th></tr></thead>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>host.platform</code></td><td >Plaftorm name (<code>win</code>, <code>linux</code>...)&#x2e;</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>host.arch</code></td><td >Plaftorm architecture (<code>x86</code>, <code>x64</code>...)&#x2e;</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>compiler.name</code></td><td >Compiler name (<code>msvc</code>, <code>gcc</code>...)&#x2e;</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>compiler.version</code></td><td >Compiler version.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="odd"><td ><code>compiler</code></td><td >Compiler identifier: <code>$${TOOLKIT.compiler.name}$${TOOLKIT.compiler.version}</code>.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top" class="even"><td ><code>mkspec</code></td><td >Toolkit mkspec shortname: <code>$${TOOLKIT.host.platform}-$${TOOLKIT.compiler}-$${TOOLKIT.host.arch}</code>.</td></tr>
</table></div>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">msvc: greaterThan( TOOLKIT.compiler.version, 2012 }: \
    message( &quot;Compiler MSVC 2013 or later detected&quot; )</pre>
<p>Note that any <code>TOOLKIT</code> property may be queried from a qmake command line, by passing the <code>QUERY_TOOLKIT_PROPERTY=</code><i>property</i> argument. For example, the following command line returns the <code>TOOLKIT.mkpsec</code> value used in the current project:</p>
<pre class="cpp">qmake QUERY_TOOLKIT_PROPERTY=mkspec</pre>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite properties values of this variable.</p><a name="pro-file-name"></a>
<h2 id="pro-file-name">_PRO_FILE_NAME_</h2>
<p>Contains the base name of the project file in use, without extension.</p>
<p>For example, the following line causes the base name of the project file to be written to the console:</p>
<pre class="cpp">message( $${_PRO_FILE_NAME_} )</pre>
<p><b>Note: </b>Do not attempt to overwrite the value of this variable.</p></div>
